---

### Phase 3: Validation Schemas

#### [NEW] [validations.ts](file:///d:/projects%20in%202026/visionboard/src/lib/validations.ts)
- Zod schemas for every API request body:
  - `registerSchema`: name (2-50 chars), email (valid format), password (8+ chars, 1 uppercase, 1 number)
  - `loginSchema`: email, password
  - `habitSchema`: name (1-100 chars), emoji (1 char), frequency (daily|weekly)
  - `toggleSchema`: date (YYYY-MM-DD format validation)
  - `routineSchema`: period (morning|afternoon|evening), name, timeEstimate (positive number or null)
  - `reorderSchema`: period, itemIds (array of valid ObjectId strings)

---

### Phase 4: Auth API Routes

#### [NEW] [auth.ts](file:///d:/projects%20in%202026/visionboard/src/lib/auth.ts)
- NextAuth configuration with CredentialsProvider
- JWT strategy with `userId` in the token payload
- Session callback to expose `userId` to the client

#### [NEW] [middleware.ts](file:///d:/projects%20in%202026/visionboard/src/middleware.ts)
- Next.js middleware that protects `/api/habits/*`, `/api/routines/*`
- Redirects unauthenticated users to `/login`
- Allows `/api/auth/*`, `/login`, `/register` through

#### [NEW] Register route — `src/app/api/auth/register/route.ts`
- Validates with Zod, checks duplicate email, hashes password, creates user, returns JWT

#### [NEW] Login route — `src/app/api/auth/login/route.ts`
- Validates credentials, compares password hash, returns JWT

#### [NEW] Me route — `src/app/api/auth/me/route.ts`
- Returns current user profile from JWT

#### [NEW] [auth.test.ts](file:///d:/projects%20in%202026/visionboard/__tests__/api/auth.test.ts)
- Tests: register success, duplicate email 409, weak password 400, login success, wrong password 401, /me with valid token, /me without token 401

---

### Phase 5: Habits API Routes

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/habits/route.ts` (GET + POST)
- `GET`: Fetch all habits for the authenticated user, sorted by `createdAt` desc
- `POST`: Validate with Zod, create habit with `userId` from JWT

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/habits/[id]/route.ts` (PUT + DELETE)
- `PUT`: Validate ownership (`userId` match), update name/emoji/frequency
- `DELETE`: Validate ownership, delete habit

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/habits/[id]/toggle/route.ts` (PATCH)
- Toggle a specific date's completion status
- If date exists in completions map → remove it; if not → add `true`

#### [NEW] [habits.test.ts](file:///d:/projects%20in%202026/visionboard/__tests__/api/habits.test.ts)
- Tests: create habit, list habits (only own), update habit, delete habit, toggle completion on/off, auth required for all, can't access another user's habits

