## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **MongoDB Atlas Setup Required**: You'll need a MongoDB Atlas account (free tier is sufficient). I'll create a `.env.example` with the required variables, but you'll need to provide the actual `MONGODB_URI` connection string.

> [!WARNING]
> **Breaking Change — localStorage Migration**: Once the backend is integrated, existing localStorage data will be orphaned. Users will need to re-create their habits/routines after registering. If you want a migration tool, let me know and I'll add a "one-click import from localStorage" feature to the plan.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Authentication Provider Choice**: The plan uses email/password (Credentials Provider). Would you also like OAuth providers (Google, GitHub) for social login? This is easy to add with NextAuth but changes the registration flow.

